// Description: This script generates a 2D spline using a set of control points defined by the user.
// Author: Tim Olson
// Date :2025-09-07
//Notes:  This is a basic example demonstrating how to use the Spline function.

// ---------------- Setup ----------------
Units(1[mm]);          // Keep scale predictable across drawings
Input();               // Stand-alone part (no external parameters)

 
// ---------------- Spline ----------------
 
Spline2D = Spline(
  Point(0, 0),
  Point(2, 2),
  Point(3, 6),
  Point(4, 10),
  Point(5, 0)
);


// ---------------- Output ----------------
Output(Spline2D);      // Output the curve to the drawing
